WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.208 align:middle line:90%
[ Silence ]

00:00:08.208 --> 00:00:17.284 align:middle line:90%
[ Music ]

00:00:24.491 --> 00:00:25.592 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa Garr: Hi.

00:00:25.592 --> 00:00:27.394 align:middle line:84%
I'm Lisa Garr, host
of Gaiam Inspirations.

00:00:27.394 --> 00:00:30.730 align:middle line:84%
And my guest today believes
that fast foods, and fad diets,

00:00:30.730 --> 00:00:33.800 align:middle line:84%
and a lack of time
or knowledge has led

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:36.236 align:middle line:90%
to America's obesity epidemic.

00:00:36.236 --> 00:00:39.272 align:middle line:84%
Healthy lifestyle expert,
Danette May is my guest.

00:00:39.272 --> 00:00:42.375 align:middle line:84%
And her solution is a cookbook
she calls, "Eat, Drink,

00:00:42.375 --> 00:00:44.144 align:middle line:90%
and Shrink," and it's a cookbook

00:00:44.144 --> 00:00:47.681 align:middle line:84%
for busy people using
five ingredients or less.

00:00:47.681 --> 00:00:49.316 align:middle line:90%
My kind of cookbook [laughter].

00:00:49.316 --> 00:00:51.952 align:middle line:84%
However, Danette is more
than just a healthy cook;

00:00:51.952 --> 00:00:54.988 align:middle line:84%
she's an inspiration to
us in many, many ways.

00:00:54.988 --> 00:00:55.989 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the show.

00:00:55.989 --> 00:00:57.390 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for being here today.

00:00:57.390 --> 00:00:59.092 align:middle line:84%
>> Danette May: Thank
you for having me, Lisa.

00:00:59.092 --> 00:01:01.061 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa Garr: Have you always
been into health and fitness?

00:01:01.061 --> 00:01:03.262 align:middle line:84%
Has this been your
lifelong journey?

00:01:03.262 --> 00:01:05.665 align:middle line:84%
>> Danette May: Yes, I've
always been into health.

00:01:05.665 --> 00:01:09.603 align:middle line:84%
And, I guess, at an early age,
I kind of knew within my heart

00:01:09.603 --> 00:01:12.906 align:middle line:84%
that I was going to be using
this as my catalyst in my life,

00:01:12.906 --> 00:01:15.742 align:middle line:84%
and -- but I've not always
been a healthy person.

00:01:15.742 --> 00:01:16.976 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa Garr: Yeah, I
mean, because sometimes...

00:01:16.976 --> 00:01:18.044 align:middle line:90%
>> Danette May: Yeah.

00:01:18.044 --> 00:01:19.446 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa Garr: ...we
need an inspiration,

00:01:19.446 --> 00:01:21.782 align:middle line:84%
some model out there that gives
us an idea of what health is.

00:01:21.782 --> 00:01:23.450 align:middle line:84%
Did you have that
model when you were...

00:01:23.450 --> 00:01:24.417 align:middle line:84%
>> Danette May: I
absolutely did not.

00:01:24.417 --> 00:01:25.519 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa Garr: Did not.

00:01:25.519 --> 00:01:27.119 align:middle line:84%
>> Danette May: No,
and so, like, for me,

00:01:27.119 --> 00:01:29.189 align:middle line:84%
I used to think health
was having, like,

00:01:29.189 --> 00:01:31.825 align:middle line:84%
reduced fat Wheat Thins
and Yoplait yogurt.

00:01:31.825 --> 00:01:32.958 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa Garr: Ah.

00:01:32.958 --> 00:01:33.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Danette May: But I
have learned, and I --

00:01:33.660 --> 00:01:34.761 align:middle line:90%
after having three kids,

00:01:34.761 --> 00:01:37.030 align:middle line:84%
I look and feel better
than I did before...

00:01:37.030 --> 00:01:38.398 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa Garr: Amazing.

00:01:38.398 --> 00:01:39.232 align:middle line:84%
>> Danette May: ...because of
learning these help things,

00:01:39.232 --> 00:01:41.401 align:middle line:90%
and movement, and all of that.

00:01:41.401 --> 00:01:43.537 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa Garr: So, okay, so
what type of -- then you --

00:01:43.537 --> 00:01:45.872 align:middle line:84%
you got into the fitness
industry, and you teach people.

00:01:45.872 --> 00:01:48.275 align:middle line:84%
What is the biggest concern
that people come to you

00:01:48.275 --> 00:01:52.312 align:middle line:84%
with when they seek you out as
a trainer or your information?

00:01:52.312 --> 00:01:53.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Danette May: What
I think most people

00:01:53.580 --> 00:01:56.349 align:middle line:84%
when they seek me out,
they're kind of like everybody.

00:01:56.349 --> 00:01:59.186 align:middle line:84%
For especially women, it's
I want to look better.

00:01:59.186 --> 00:02:02.589 align:middle line:84%
But it's -- what I help them
with is not that you just want

00:02:02.589 --> 00:02:05.458 align:middle line:84%
to look better on the outside,
because it's deeper than that.

00:02:05.458 --> 00:02:07.427 align:middle line:84%
We say, "I want to lose
20 pounds," but, really,

00:02:07.427 --> 00:02:10.029 align:middle line:84%
why do you want to
lose 20 pounds?

00:02:10.029 --> 00:02:11.865 align:middle line:84%
It's -- you know, I'm
finding that people,

00:02:11.865 --> 00:02:13.200 align:middle line:90%
if you dig a little deeper,

00:02:13.200 --> 00:02:15.669 align:middle line:84%
then they know why they
actually are seeking me out is

00:02:15.669 --> 00:02:18.205 align:middle line:84%
to feel confident,
to feel on purpose,

00:02:18.205 --> 00:02:19.739 align:middle line:90%
to self-love themselves...

00:02:19.739 --> 00:02:20.840 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:02:20.840 --> 00:02:21.608 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: ...and to feel
wanted and desired.

00:02:21.608 --> 00:02:22.142 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:02:22.142 --> 00:02:22.976 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:02:22.976 --> 00:02:24.277 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: So it comes down to that.

00:02:24.277 --> 00:02:25.879 align:middle line:84%
So, you help people really
get fit from the inside out,

00:02:25.879 --> 00:02:28.615 align:middle line:84%
rather than just what
they see on the outside.

00:02:28.615 --> 00:02:29.316 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Absolutely.

00:02:29.316 --> 00:02:30.817 align:middle line:90%
I try to hit that first.

00:02:30.817 --> 00:02:32.152 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:02:32.152 --> 00:02:34.087 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's only so much
that you can do when you --

00:02:34.087 --> 00:02:35.355 align:middle line:84%
when it comes to
the physical body.

00:02:35.355 --> 00:02:37.991 align:middle line:84%
You can't spot reduce; you
have to look at the whole,

00:02:37.991 --> 00:02:39.726 align:middle line:90%
entire package, right?

00:02:39.726 --> 00:02:41.127 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Absolutely.

00:02:41.127 --> 00:02:44.129 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, I think when you
say the whole, entire package,

00:02:44.129 --> 00:02:47.901 align:middle line:84%
once again, we think about
this outward body of ours,

00:02:47.901 --> 00:02:49.936 align:middle line:84%
but that's not overall
health, right?

00:02:49.936 --> 00:02:53.073 align:middle line:84%
It's really about -- I think,
right now in our world,

00:02:53.073 --> 00:02:57.177 align:middle line:84%
we're spiritually starved,
and so we fill up with food.

00:02:57.177 --> 00:02:59.679 align:middle line:84%
So fill -- we're feeling there's
a void, and we don't know how

00:02:59.679 --> 00:03:02.515 align:middle line:84%
to fill it up, and a lot of
people are filling it with food.

00:03:02.515 --> 00:03:04.551 align:middle line:84%
And if we can take care
of that, it kind of takes

00:03:04.551 --> 00:03:07.821 align:middle line:84%
out all the drama that goes
around with the outside,

00:03:07.821 --> 00:03:09.389 align:middle line:84%
and what I'm eating,
and what I'm not eating,

00:03:09.389 --> 00:03:11.124 align:middle line:84%
and am I moving,
am I not moving.

00:03:11.124 --> 00:03:12.259 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right.

00:03:12.259 --> 00:03:13.727 align:middle line:84%
Do -- now, do you have
a spiritual practice,

00:03:13.727 --> 00:03:15.427 align:middle line:90%
a daily spiritual practice?

00:03:15.427 --> 00:03:16.028 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Absolutely.

00:03:16.028 --> 00:03:16.563 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: You do.

00:03:16.563 --> 00:03:17.264 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yes.

00:03:17.264 --> 00:03:18.498 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: What do you do?

00:03:18.498 --> 00:03:19.899 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: And its make all
the difference in my world.

00:03:19.899 --> 00:03:22.402 align:middle line:84%
Like when I said I feel and look
better after having three kids

00:03:22.402 --> 00:03:24.537 align:middle line:84%
than I did before; even when
I was still on this health

00:03:24.537 --> 00:03:27.874 align:middle line:84%
and fitness road, it's
completely different.

00:03:27.874 --> 00:03:31.544 align:middle line:84%
One thing, I always wake
up and have a moment

00:03:31.544 --> 00:03:33.480 align:middle line:90%
of gratitude; whatever that is.

00:03:33.480 --> 00:03:36.516 align:middle line:84%
And that, literally takes 10
seconds, because I'm the mom

00:03:36.516 --> 00:03:38.084 align:middle line:84%
that they're waking me
up sometimes [laughter].

00:03:38.084 --> 00:03:39.219 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah, yeah [inaudible].

00:03:39.219 --> 00:03:40.220 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: And before I craw
out of bed, you know,

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:41.288 align:middle line:90%
I might touch their hand,

00:03:41.288 --> 00:03:42.889 align:middle line:84%
and I say three things
I'm grateful for.

00:03:42.889 --> 00:03:44.658 align:middle line:90%
I always start with that.

00:03:44.658 --> 00:03:45.992 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Nice.

00:03:45.992 --> 00:03:47.360 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: And then, maybe there's
a bustle of the day going,

00:03:47.360 --> 00:03:49.129 align:middle line:84%
you know, getting
them out the door.

00:03:49.129 --> 00:03:52.499 align:middle line:84%
Or I'm just working, and
then I take a minute to spend

00:03:52.499 --> 00:03:55.468 align:middle line:84%
in meditation or prayer,
and do that every day.

00:03:55.468 --> 00:03:57.971 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Now, I mentioned
earlier that Danette is more

00:03:57.971 --> 00:04:00.006 align:middle line:90%
than just a fitness expert.

00:04:00.006 --> 00:04:02.742 align:middle line:84%
You've had an incredible
story that you --

00:04:02.742 --> 00:04:06.680 align:middle line:84%
and an incredible hardship
that you've come through,

00:04:06.680 --> 00:04:10.550 align:middle line:84%
that most people wouldn't have
come through to do what you do,

00:04:10.550 --> 00:04:12.919 align:middle line:84%
and all the inspiration
that you are.

00:04:12.919 --> 00:04:15.055 align:middle line:84%
And I have so much
respect for you.

00:04:15.055 --> 00:04:17.190 align:middle line:84%
If you wouldn't mind
sharing your story with us,

00:04:17.190 --> 00:04:20.860 align:middle line:84%
and how you dug yourself out
of a deep, deep depression.

00:04:20.860 --> 00:04:22.228 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Okay, yeah.

00:04:22.228 --> 00:04:24.965 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's -- it's really
-- I look back on this --

00:04:24.965 --> 00:04:27.467 align:middle line:84%
you know, I think sometimes
when we go through hard things,

00:04:27.467 --> 00:04:29.302 align:middle line:90%
you wonder why in the moment.

00:04:29.302 --> 00:04:30.403 align:middle line:90%
Why am I going through?

00:04:30.403 --> 00:04:33.239 align:middle line:84%
Why me? But now that
I'm past that moment,

00:04:33.239 --> 00:04:36.142 align:middle line:84%
and I'm looking back, I know
why I needed to go through that.

00:04:36.142 --> 00:04:36.676 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: You do?

00:04:36.676 --> 00:04:38.044 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: I do!

00:04:38.044 --> 00:04:40.146 align:middle line:84%
I really feel that there's a
message that I need to share.

00:04:40.146 --> 00:04:41.381 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:04:41.381 --> 00:04:42.882 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: And I feel like
there was that moment going

00:04:42.882 --> 00:04:44.250 align:middle line:90%
through that was kind of an Aha!

00:04:44.250 --> 00:04:46.953 align:middle line:84%
moment for me, where I
was, like, I've always been

00:04:46.953 --> 00:04:49.589 align:middle line:84%
into health and fitness; I've
always been interested in it.

00:04:49.589 --> 00:04:53.893 align:middle line:84%
And -- but now I see
how this truly heals.

00:04:53.893 --> 00:04:54.694 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Oh, okay.

00:04:54.694 --> 00:04:55.829 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Truly heals.

00:04:55.829 --> 00:04:58.031 align:middle line:84%
So, my experiences is,
is about five years ago,

00:04:58.031 --> 00:05:00.200 align:middle line:84%
I was pregnant with
my second child.

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:04.437 align:middle line:84%
And I was always really
sick during my pregnancies,

00:05:04.437 --> 00:05:06.806 align:middle line:90%
bed-ridden, can't move.

00:05:06.806 --> 00:05:08.742 align:middle line:84%
It's called hypernemesis,
where you throw up,

00:05:08.742 --> 00:05:10.477 align:middle line:90%
literally, about 10 to 15 times.

00:05:10.477 --> 00:05:11.311 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Oh, my God.

00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:13.246 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah, so very, very sick.

00:05:13.246 --> 00:05:15.682 align:middle line:84%
And so, you have to take, like,
[inaudible] cancer medications,

00:05:15.682 --> 00:05:17.117 align:middle line:90%
to keep the throw-up down.

00:05:17.117 --> 00:05:17.817 align:middle line:90%
Things like that.

00:05:17.817 --> 00:05:18.385 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:05:18.385 --> 00:05:18.918 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Crazy.

00:05:18.918 --> 00:05:20.020 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:05:20.020 --> 00:05:21.421 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: But, ready to
have my second child,

00:05:21.421 --> 00:05:25.425 align:middle line:84%
and went into the hospital
so excited, as every new --

00:05:25.425 --> 00:05:29.629 align:middle line:84%
you know, you're excited, you've
endured so much sickness and,

00:05:29.629 --> 00:05:33.299 align:middle line:84%
unfortunately, he passed
away at the hospital, and...

00:05:33.299 --> 00:05:35.468 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: After you
gave birth and...

00:05:35.468 --> 00:05:36.836 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:05:36.836 --> 00:05:38.571 align:middle line:84%
Just during that whole process,
it really stunned everyone.

00:05:38.571 --> 00:05:39.572 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:05:39.572 --> 00:05:40.906 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: It was one
of those moments.

00:05:40.906 --> 00:05:43.476 align:middle line:84%
Even doctors were, like, I
don't know what's gone wrong;

00:05:43.476 --> 00:05:44.544 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:05:44.544 --> 00:05:46.780 align:middle line:84%
And in those moments,
you go, "Why?

00:05:46.780 --> 00:05:50.517 align:middle line:84%
Why?And, you know, I don't know
that necessarily had an Aha!

00:05:50.517 --> 00:05:51.451 align:middle line:90%
moment in that time.

00:05:51.451 --> 00:05:52.452 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: No, I'm sure.

00:05:52.452 --> 00:05:52.952 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:05:52.952 --> 00:05:54.320 align:middle line:90%
But...

00:05:54.320 --> 00:05:55.555 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: I mean, it's -- it was
probably so shocking to you

00:05:55.555 --> 00:05:58.324 align:middle line:84%
that you weren't looking
for the why at that point.

00:05:58.324 --> 00:06:01.361 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: No, I was just,
you know, for me,

00:06:01.361 --> 00:06:06.066 align:middle line:84%
I've always been really pretty
happy person, and loved to move,

00:06:06.066 --> 00:06:07.367 align:middle line:90%
and loved to be outside.

00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:11.137 align:middle line:84%
And I found myself for
months literally not wanting

00:06:11.137 --> 00:06:12.505 align:middle line:90%
to get out of bed.

00:06:12.505 --> 00:06:15.008 align:middle line:84%
And I don't really
know if I knew I was

00:06:15.008 --> 00:06:17.544 align:middle line:84%
in a depression,
but obviously I was.

00:06:17.544 --> 00:06:22.882 align:middle line:84%
And I just remember the day
that I was, like, I really need

00:06:22.882 --> 00:06:24.517 align:middle line:84%
to get out and go for
just a walk around.

00:06:24.517 --> 00:06:25.885 align:middle line:84%
You know, you're body's
gone through all the...

00:06:25.885 --> 00:06:26.886 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Well, you were still...

00:06:26.886 --> 00:06:27.420 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: ...changes
of having a baby.

00:06:27.420 --> 00:06:27.954 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:06:27.954 --> 00:06:29.355 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:06:29.355 --> 00:06:30.656 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And you were -- you were
still probably producing milk,

00:06:30.656 --> 00:06:31.191 align:middle line:90%
you...

00:06:31.191 --> 00:06:32.592 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:06:32.592 --> 00:06:35.528 align:middle line:84%
My body ached to have this baby,
so it was a constant reminder,

00:06:35.528 --> 00:06:37.630 align:middle line:84%
not only emotionally,
but physically.

00:06:37.630 --> 00:06:41.034 align:middle line:84%
And so, it was very, very
difficult at that time for me.

00:06:41.034 --> 00:06:43.369 align:middle line:84%
And it was one of those moments
for me where I was, like, wow,

00:06:43.369 --> 00:06:45.305 align:middle line:90%
I've been dealt my card.

00:06:45.305 --> 00:06:46.940 align:middle line:84%
And what am I going
to do with this?

00:06:46.940 --> 00:06:47.841 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Oh, my gosh.

00:06:47.841 --> 00:06:49.142 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:06:49.142 --> 00:06:51.644 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So, you came home,
and you were -- you just --

00:06:51.644 --> 00:06:54.481 align:middle line:90%
you came home without a child.

00:06:54.481 --> 00:06:58.818 align:middle line:84%
You came home, in that moment
when -- what did you do?

00:06:58.818 --> 00:07:02.155 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: In that moment, I
didn't do much, you know,

00:07:02.155 --> 00:07:06.359 align:middle line:84%
I was in a survival
mode, and I didn't move.

00:07:06.359 --> 00:07:09.395 align:middle line:84%
I didn't eat sometimes;
I maybe ate

00:07:09.395 --> 00:07:12.298 align:middle line:84%
if someone brought
something to me.

00:07:12.298 --> 00:07:15.702 align:middle line:90%
I just was in kind of a fog.

00:07:15.702 --> 00:07:18.271 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Now, were you a fitness
teacher before this, or?

00:07:18.271 --> 00:07:19.472 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yes.

00:07:19.472 --> 00:07:21.641 align:middle line:84%
I had always done fitness,
and I think that's kind

00:07:21.641 --> 00:07:25.678 align:middle line:84%
of what I believe is, like,
it's really easy to be involved

00:07:25.678 --> 00:07:27.947 align:middle line:84%
in exercise and be like, okay,
I'm going to eat this and this,

00:07:27.947 --> 00:07:29.682 align:middle line:84%
when everything in your
world is going great.

00:07:29.682 --> 00:07:32.285 align:middle line:84%
And it was easy for me
to teach people that

00:07:32.285 --> 00:07:36.523 align:middle line:84%
and to share this message and --
but it wasn't until I was, like,

00:07:36.523 --> 00:07:40.193 align:middle line:84%
whoa, like, my body is
so far out of alignment.

00:07:40.193 --> 00:07:44.097 align:middle line:84%
I am totally out of shape;
I don't feel good; I --

00:07:44.097 --> 00:07:47.634 align:middle line:84%
emotionally, physically, all
those things, and spiritually.

00:07:47.634 --> 00:07:48.468 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right, yes.

00:07:48.468 --> 00:07:50.703 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: What am I going to do?

00:07:50.703 --> 00:07:53.239 align:middle line:84%
And I -- you know, this is
where all this comes about,

00:07:53.239 --> 00:07:55.174 align:middle line:84%
because I went out
-- I decided to go

00:07:55.174 --> 00:07:57.210 align:middle line:90%
for a walk just around my block.

00:07:57.210 --> 00:08:00.013 align:middle line:84%
And it -- I always
say it sounds cliche,

00:08:00.013 --> 00:08:02.115 align:middle line:84%
because it really was
that moment for me.

00:08:02.115 --> 00:08:05.084 align:middle line:84%
Because everything -- I, like,
remember the houses I passed;

00:08:05.084 --> 00:08:07.520 align:middle line:90%
I remember the birds singing,

00:08:07.520 --> 00:08:11.324 align:middle line:84%
and it was like my heart was
opening, literally, just opening

00:08:11.324 --> 00:08:12.392 align:middle line:90%
for the first time, and it...

00:08:12.392 --> 00:08:13.626 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Hadn't felt
for that long.

00:08:13.626 --> 00:08:15.028 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:08:15.028 --> 00:08:16.896 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: How long after you came
home did you go for that walk?

00:08:16.896 --> 00:08:19.198 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: Probably around
three months.

00:08:19.198 --> 00:08:19.899 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:08:19.899 --> 00:08:20.633 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Three months...

00:08:20.633 --> 00:08:21.834 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:08:21.834 --> 00:08:22.502 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: ...of really not
wanting to talk to people.

00:08:22.502 --> 00:08:23.736 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Uh-uh.

00:08:23.736 --> 00:08:25.738 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: I didn't really
know what to say, you know?

00:08:25.738 --> 00:08:27.507 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: What about
your child at home?

00:08:27.507 --> 00:08:28.708 align:middle line:84%
You had a daughter
already, right?

00:08:28.708 --> 00:08:29.676 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah [brief laughter].

00:08:29.676 --> 00:08:30.810 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: And she was how old?

00:08:30.810 --> 00:08:33.212 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: She was around
four, yeah, at the time.

00:08:33.212 --> 00:08:34.914 align:middle line:90%
Four, four and a half.

00:08:34.914 --> 00:08:37.950 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, so it was really difficult
for her, too, you know,

00:08:37.950 --> 00:08:40.152 align:middle line:90%
I always call her an old soul.

00:08:40.152 --> 00:08:43.089 align:middle line:84%
She was going through her
own mourning, as well.

00:08:43.089 --> 00:08:44.057 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Oh, my God.

00:08:44.057 --> 00:08:46.292 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: So, you know
it's bad to say,

00:08:46.292 --> 00:08:48.394 align:middle line:84%
but I don't even remember
what she was doing

00:08:48.394 --> 00:08:50.196 align:middle line:84%
in those three months,
poor child, but...

00:08:50.196 --> 00:08:50.697 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right, right.

00:08:50.697 --> 00:08:51.230 align:middle line:90%
No, no.

00:08:51.230 --> 00:08:52.098 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:08:52.098 --> 00:08:53.232 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: That's an
important point,

00:08:53.232 --> 00:08:55.034 align:middle line:84%
is that she was grieving,
you were grieving.

00:08:55.034 --> 00:08:58.371 align:middle line:84%
Who has the tools to
handle something like that?

00:08:58.371 --> 00:09:01.107 align:middle line:90%
I mean, who has those tools?

00:09:01.107 --> 00:09:03.676 align:middle line:84%
It's very challenging
in that moment.

00:09:03.676 --> 00:09:08.081 align:middle line:84%
So, just by going on that walk
and beginning to feel, and hear,

00:09:08.081 --> 00:09:11.417 align:middle line:84%
and smell again, was just one
baby step at a time, right?

00:09:11.417 --> 00:09:15.221 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: Yeah, and I knew, like
I said, it was like this Aha!

00:09:15.221 --> 00:09:19.092 align:middle line:84%
moment of -- I knew
and, you know,

00:09:19.092 --> 00:09:20.693 align:middle line:90%
you know that movement heals.

00:09:20.693 --> 00:09:22.762 align:middle line:84%
You know movement
cures depression.

00:09:22.762 --> 00:09:25.565 align:middle line:84%
You hear it, but until you go
through it, and you feel it,

00:09:25.565 --> 00:09:29.002 align:middle line:84%
you're like, this is really
true, and this is what's going

00:09:29.002 --> 00:09:30.503 align:middle line:90%
to heal me, is moving.

00:09:30.503 --> 00:09:32.639 align:middle line:84%
And I just started with
walking around the block.

00:09:32.639 --> 00:09:33.439 align:middle line:90%
That's all I could do.

00:09:33.439 --> 00:09:35.341 align:middle line:90%
And it was, like, I see now,

00:09:35.341 --> 00:09:37.477 align:middle line:84%
I see how this is
going to heal me.

00:09:37.477 --> 00:09:40.413 align:middle line:84%
I see what other people
must be experiencing,

00:09:40.413 --> 00:09:42.915 align:middle line:84%
and I'm feeling it
for the first time.

00:09:42.915 --> 00:09:47.787 align:middle line:84%
And I knew, too, that I needed
to eat well to get through this,

00:09:47.787 --> 00:09:49.889 align:middle line:84%
that I needed healing
energy foods

00:09:49.889 --> 00:09:52.558 align:middle line:84%
to not just make me look
good -- I was out of shape --

00:09:52.558 --> 00:09:54.761 align:middle line:84%
but to make me feel
good spiritually,

00:09:54.761 --> 00:09:57.263 align:middle line:90%
and whole, and heal, basically.

00:09:57.263 --> 00:09:59.866 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And so, between the
movement and the walking, it --

00:09:59.866 --> 00:10:01.801 align:middle line:90%
and the walking, and the foods

00:10:01.801 --> 00:10:05.538 align:middle line:84%
that you knew made you feel a
little bit better, how long did

00:10:05.538 --> 00:10:08.775 align:middle line:84%
that take you to start to feel
alive again, to start to feel

00:10:08.775 --> 00:10:11.944 align:middle line:84%
like you want to go even
out in the world again?

00:10:11.944 --> 00:10:14.647 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: You know, it
really -- it's amazing.

00:10:14.647 --> 00:10:15.848 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't take that long.

00:10:15.848 --> 00:10:17.250 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: It doesn't?

00:10:17.250 --> 00:10:19.118 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: If you really feel the
difference of not feeling good,

00:10:19.118 --> 00:10:23.523 align:middle line:84%
and then you start just three
days of eating alive food --

00:10:23.523 --> 00:10:25.024 align:middle line:90%
food that's energy driven.

00:10:25.024 --> 00:10:26.292 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Three days.

00:10:26.292 --> 00:10:28.861 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: Three days and just
moving, I got a little bit

00:10:28.861 --> 00:10:31.030 align:middle line:84%
of that, "Mm, yes,
I want to do this.

00:10:31.030 --> 00:10:32.165 align:middle line:90%
I feel this."

00:10:32.165 --> 00:10:33.833 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't like I was all
happy again [laughter].

00:10:33.833 --> 00:10:34.634 align:middle line:90%
But I was...

00:10:34.634 --> 00:10:35.902 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Well, yeah.

00:10:35.902 --> 00:10:36.869 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: I was actually feeling
it within myself enough

00:10:36.869 --> 00:10:39.138 align:middle line:90%
to go, "This is what I want.

00:10:39.138 --> 00:10:41.074 align:middle line:90%
This is what I need to share."

00:10:41.074 --> 00:10:43.076 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Did it get any
easier at that point?

00:10:43.076 --> 00:10:45.345 align:middle line:84%
Did you still have a
rocky path to go through

00:10:45.345 --> 00:10:46.646 align:middle line:90%
and things to deal with?

00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:48.414 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: You always
-- you always do.

00:10:48.414 --> 00:10:52.452 align:middle line:84%
I mean, even if you are dealt
with the hard card such as that,

00:10:52.452 --> 00:10:53.986 align:middle line:84%
those are going to
be other ones, right?

00:10:53.986 --> 00:10:55.655 align:middle line:84%
You're going to get
dealt other things.

00:10:55.655 --> 00:10:57.323 align:middle line:90%
Life is life, and --

00:10:57.323 --> 00:11:00.026 align:middle line:84%
but I realized I am so
much more equipped to deal

00:11:00.026 --> 00:11:02.361 align:middle line:84%
with the hard things in
life when I have, you know,

00:11:02.361 --> 00:11:05.698 align:middle line:84%
good movement and good,
healthy food in my arsenal.

00:11:05.698 --> 00:11:06.232 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:11:06.232 --> 00:11:07.567 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:11:07.567 --> 00:11:09.235 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Well, let's take a look
at Danette in action here.

00:11:09.235 --> 00:11:11.437 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:11:11.437 --> 00:11:12.071 align:middle line:84%
>> [Video] [Background
Music] Hi!

00:11:12.071 --> 00:11:13.473 align:middle line:90%
Danette May, here.

00:11:13.473 --> 00:11:16.809 align:middle line:84%
Today, I want to share with you
some tips on portion control.

00:11:16.809 --> 00:11:19.212 align:middle line:84%
What I'm really finding when
people are starting to adjust

00:11:19.212 --> 00:11:22.181 align:middle line:84%
into trying to get
healthier, to lose weight,

00:11:22.181 --> 00:11:24.183 align:middle line:90%
is they lose track on portions.

00:11:24.183 --> 00:11:26.686 align:middle line:84%
And they don't really know
what a correct portion is.

00:11:26.686 --> 00:11:28.221 align:middle line:84%
You know, you see, oh,
I need to eat three

00:11:28.221 --> 00:11:30.056 align:middle line:90%
to four ounces of protein.

00:11:30.056 --> 00:11:31.557 align:middle line:90%
What does that really mean?

00:11:31.557 --> 00:11:34.961 align:middle line:84%
And how do I measure all this
if I'm traveling all the time?

00:11:34.961 --> 00:11:36.362 align:middle line:84%
I know it can get
really confusing,

00:11:36.362 --> 00:11:39.031 align:middle line:84%
but portion control is
really, really important

00:11:39.031 --> 00:11:41.734 align:middle line:90%
if you're trying to lose weight.

00:11:41.734 --> 00:11:45.004 align:middle line:84%
Our bodies really don't need
as many calories and as big

00:11:45.004 --> 00:11:47.540 align:middle line:84%
of amounts as we really think
we should have [laughter].

00:11:47.540 --> 00:11:48.641 align:middle line:90%
It needs less.

00:11:48.641 --> 00:11:50.409 align:middle line:84%
And so, I have one
recommendation,

00:11:50.409 --> 00:11:52.812 align:middle line:84%
is to choose a smaller
plate to eat with.

00:11:52.812 --> 00:11:54.046 align:middle line:90%
That's really going to help you.

00:11:54.046 --> 00:11:57.216 align:middle line:84%
You shouldn't eat a
whole plate full --

00:11:57.216 --> 00:11:59.218 align:middle line:84%
the standard plates that
you buy at the store.

00:11:59.218 --> 00:12:01.821 align:middle line:84%
You should choose what they
usually call a salad plate

00:12:01.821 --> 00:12:03.589 align:middle line:90%
to put your dinner portions on.

00:12:03.589 --> 00:12:04.757 align:middle line:90%
That's number one.

00:12:04.757 --> 00:12:07.059 align:middle line:84%
The next tip I'd like to
use is just your hand.

00:12:07.059 --> 00:12:09.529 align:middle line:84%
Your hand is portable; it's
the easiest measuring device

00:12:09.529 --> 00:12:10.797 align:middle line:90%
you have.

00:12:10.797 --> 00:12:12.565 align:middle line:84%
So, when someone mentions
that you should have three

00:12:12.565 --> 00:12:16.302 align:middle line:84%
to four ounces, like I usually
do in my book, of protein,

00:12:16.302 --> 00:12:19.772 align:middle line:84%
that is the size of your palm;
the thickness of your palm,

00:12:19.772 --> 00:12:22.108 align:middle line:90%
and the size of your palm.

00:12:22.108 --> 00:12:25.111 align:middle line:84%
Or, you can use the
estimate of a deck of cards.

00:12:25.111 --> 00:12:29.882 align:middle line:84%
That is three ounces of meat
-- of protein, of red meat.

00:12:29.882 --> 00:12:34.187 align:middle line:84%
If I'm mentioning a
tablespoon of fat, that would be

00:12:34.187 --> 00:12:37.190 align:middle line:84%
about the size of the
tip of your thumb,

00:12:37.190 --> 00:12:38.891 align:middle line:90%
so a tablespoon, all right?

00:12:38.891 --> 00:12:40.259 align:middle line:84%
I know some people have
bigger hands or not,

00:12:40.259 --> 00:12:41.294 align:middle line:90%
but that gives you a --

00:12:41.294 --> 00:12:42.695 align:middle line:84%
you don't have to be
so strict with it.

00:12:42.695 --> 00:12:46.699 align:middle line:84%
I think people get so carried
away with being so exact,

00:12:46.699 --> 00:12:48.201 align:middle line:90%
that it takes the fun out of it,

00:12:48.201 --> 00:12:49.902 align:middle line:84%
and it makes you
feel so regimented.

00:12:49.902 --> 00:12:52.605 align:middle line:84%
And this isn't meant to be
regimented if you just kind

00:12:52.605 --> 00:12:53.739 align:middle line:90%
of take those equations.

00:12:53.739 --> 00:12:56.042 align:middle line:84%
If I say a handful,
just take a handful.

00:12:56.042 --> 00:12:57.643 align:middle line:90%
It's not heaping, right?

00:12:57.643 --> 00:13:00.246 align:middle line:84%
It's just a handful of
nuts, and there you go;

00:13:00.246 --> 00:13:02.748 align:middle line:84%
you've got a great snack
and protein source.

00:13:02.748 --> 00:13:06.352 align:middle line:84%
A cup. So, I like to, like,
hold my hand like this.

00:13:06.352 --> 00:13:09.956 align:middle line:84%
And that -- filling up
that cup inside my hands is

00:13:09.956 --> 00:13:11.357 align:middle line:90%
about approximately a cup.

00:13:11.357 --> 00:13:15.695 align:middle line:84%
If I mention a cup of veggies,
that's about a cup of veggies.

00:13:15.695 --> 00:13:19.632 align:middle line:84%
So, these just is simple tips
that you can do to really stay

00:13:19.632 --> 00:13:23.502 align:middle line:84%
on track with losing weight and
staying within portion control.

00:13:23.502 --> 00:13:26.539 align:middle line:84%
Just remember, stay on top
of your journey; you're going

00:13:26.539 --> 00:13:28.207 align:middle line:84%
to get there; you're
going to learn it.

00:13:28.207 --> 00:13:30.676 align:middle line:84%
It's just like riding a
bike; it's hard at first,

00:13:30.676 --> 00:13:32.778 align:middle line:84%
but then you become
super-efficient at it,

00:13:32.778 --> 00:13:34.447 align:middle line:84%
and just remember
you have your hand,

00:13:34.447 --> 00:13:36.515 align:middle line:84%
and it's portable,
and just have fun.

