00:29:57.062 --> 00:29:58.363 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Exactly.

00:29:58.363 --> 00:29:59.865 align:middle line:84%
So, yeah, a lot of
them are junk.

00:29:59.865 --> 00:30:02.033 align:middle line:90%
Like, I think of -- in 2011,

00:30:02.033 --> 00:30:07.439 align:middle line:84%
the biggest fitness piece
was the Shake Weight.

00:30:07.439 --> 00:30:08.139 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:30:08.139 --> 00:30:09.541 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Not effective.

00:30:09.541 --> 00:30:13.111 align:middle line:84%
So that certainly doesn't really
work for what it was claiming,

00:30:13.111 --> 00:30:16.147 align:middle line:84%
but it was the number
one seller in 2011.

00:30:16.147 --> 00:30:16.781 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Interesting.

00:30:16.781 --> 00:30:18.149 align:middle line:90%
So what does work?

00:30:18.149 --> 00:30:20.819 align:middle line:84%
Well, what you said earlier,
the four days a week doing...

00:30:20.819 --> 00:30:21.920 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: You know, yeah.

00:30:21.920 --> 00:30:25.590 align:middle line:84%
What works is one; 80
% of what you eat --

00:30:25.590 --> 00:30:27.959 align:middle line:84%
that's going to be
80 % of your results.

00:30:27.959 --> 00:30:32.030 align:middle line:84%
So what you eat is the
most critical thing.

00:30:32.030 --> 00:30:33.899 align:middle line:84%
Abs are truly made
in the kitchen.

00:30:33.899 --> 00:30:34.866 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Huh.

00:30:34.866 --> 00:30:35.533 align:middle line:90%
Really?

00:30:35.533 --> 00:30:36.801 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Absolutely.

00:30:36.801 --> 00:30:39.738 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So can you just eat
correctly and not exercise

00:30:39.738 --> 00:30:41.973 align:middle line:84%
and still have the
results you want?

00:30:41.973 --> 00:30:44.476 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: Depends on the results
because for me, personally,

00:30:44.476 --> 00:30:46.378 align:middle line:90%
I believe in that whole package.

00:30:46.378 --> 00:30:47.779 align:middle line:90%
It's not just about your body.

00:30:47.779 --> 00:30:50.815 align:middle line:84%
It's about your mind,
your heart, and your soul.

00:30:50.815 --> 00:30:51.983 align:middle line:90%
Do you want ultimate health?

00:30:51.983 --> 00:30:53.785 align:middle line:90%
You want to feel good,

00:30:53.785 --> 00:30:56.888 align:middle line:84%
it's about not just looking
good, but feeling good.

00:30:56.888 --> 00:31:01.493 align:middle line:84%
So, I recommend 15 to 20
minutes of effective movement

00:31:01.493 --> 00:31:03.795 align:middle line:84%
at least three times
a week at the minimum.

00:31:03.795 --> 00:31:05.130 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Okay.

00:31:05.130 --> 00:31:06.431 align:middle line:84%
Now, when you're eating and
you're cooking and so forth,

00:31:06.431 --> 00:31:08.099 align:middle line:90%
you talk about mindful eating.

00:31:08.099 --> 00:31:09.935 align:middle line:90%
What is mindful eating?

00:31:09.935 --> 00:31:11.903 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: Mindful eating,
in my opinion --

00:31:11.903 --> 00:31:14.506 align:middle line:84%
cause you can talk about it,
you might have heard about it --

00:31:14.506 --> 00:31:16.908 align:middle line:84%
it was when you just
think about your food --

00:31:16.908 --> 00:31:18.209 align:middle line:90%
what's going in your mouth.

00:31:18.209 --> 00:31:19.044 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right.

00:31:19.044 --> 00:31:19.577 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: That's one piece of it.

00:31:19.577 --> 00:31:20.345 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Okay.

00:31:20.345 --> 00:31:21.379 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: But the other piece

00:31:21.379 --> 00:31:24.883 align:middle line:84%
to me is what you do
put on your plate.

00:31:24.883 --> 00:31:28.320 align:middle line:84%
Because, ultimately our body
tells us what it wants --

00:31:28.320 --> 00:31:30.021 align:middle line:90%
are you listening to your body?

00:31:30.021 --> 00:31:33.792 align:middle line:84%
Are you really loving yourself
enough to give yourself the best

00:31:33.792 --> 00:31:36.494 align:middle line:84%
of what your body needs
to live its purpose,

00:31:36.494 --> 00:31:39.431 align:middle line:84%
to have enough energy, to have
enough clarity in the mind?

00:31:39.431 --> 00:31:41.967 align:middle line:84%
That's the first step
of being mindful.

00:31:41.967 --> 00:31:42.934 align:middle line:90%
What do I put on my plate?

00:31:42.934 --> 00:31:44.235 align:middle line:84%
What do I put in
my shopping cart?

00:31:44.235 --> 00:31:45.170 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right.

00:31:45.170 --> 00:31:46.504 align:middle line:84%
I was going to ask
you about that.

00:31:46.504 --> 00:31:48.873 align:middle line:84%
So, if you were to go into
someone's kitchen right now --

00:31:48.873 --> 00:31:50.175 align:middle line:90%
what would you throw away?

00:31:50.175 --> 00:31:50.942 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Not much.

00:31:50.942 --> 00:31:52.010 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Like, what are some

00:31:52.010 --> 00:31:53.378 align:middle line:84%
of the things you
would just throw away?

00:31:53.378 --> 00:31:55.180 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: Well, not to the fault
of someone in their kitchen

00:31:55.180 --> 00:31:57.148 align:middle line:84%
because media has
done an awesome job

00:31:57.148 --> 00:31:59.250 align:middle line:84%
of misinforming us
-- and its marketing.

00:31:59.250 --> 00:32:00.819 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they're trying
to sell their product

00:32:00.819 --> 00:32:02.253 align:middle line:90%
and they're doing a good job.

00:32:02.253 --> 00:32:04.823 align:middle line:84%
So the first thing I'd probably
find is artificial sweetener

00:32:04.823 --> 00:32:06.224 align:middle line:90%
in someone's kitchen.

00:32:06.224 --> 00:32:09.494 align:middle line:84%
Splenda that they use in baking
or whatever they're putting

00:32:09.494 --> 00:32:12.130 align:middle line:84%
in their coffee that they
think is low fat and,

00:32:12.130 --> 00:32:13.365 align:middle line:90%
you know, no calories.

00:32:13.365 --> 00:32:14.933 align:middle line:90%
I would clear that out ASAP.

00:32:14.933 --> 00:32:15.433 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Okay.

00:32:15.433 --> 00:32:16.501 align:middle line:90%
Okay.

00:32:16.501 --> 00:32:17.669 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: I would clear
out any diet sodas.

00:32:17.669 --> 00:32:21.539 align:middle line:84%
Okay. Most people
have diet soda, right,

00:32:21.539 --> 00:32:24.442 align:middle line:84%
because they think it's
going to make them slim.

00:32:24.442 --> 00:32:25.010 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Uh huh.

00:32:25.010 --> 00:32:26.144 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Not true.

00:32:26.144 --> 00:32:27.746 align:middle line:84%
I would throw out that,
and I would throw out --

00:32:27.746 --> 00:32:30.448 align:middle line:84%
this might surprise you
-- everything wheat bread.

00:32:30.448 --> 00:32:33.651 align:middle line:84%
I think we think that
wheat bread is healthy.

00:32:33.651 --> 00:32:34.619 align:middle line:90%
I would throw that out.

00:32:34.619 --> 00:32:35.420 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: You mean wheat,
whole wheat,

00:32:35.420 --> 00:32:36.988 align:middle line:90%
grain, whole grain bread...

00:32:36.988 --> 00:32:38.356 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Like whole wheat bread.

00:32:38.356 --> 00:32:40.925 align:middle line:84%
Throw that out and
anything white, of course.

00:32:40.925 --> 00:32:42.160 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Of course.

00:32:42.160 --> 00:32:44.262 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's something
that people might not know.

00:32:44.262 --> 00:32:46.731 align:middle line:84%
So, why would you throw out
the wheat and the white bread?

00:32:46.731 --> 00:32:47.932 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Well.

00:32:47.932 --> 00:32:50.402 align:middle line:84%
Okay. So, I think most of
us know that white bread

00:32:50.402 --> 00:32:54.506 align:middle line:84%
and white flours and maybe white
rice -- they're higher glycogens

00:32:54.506 --> 00:32:56.608 align:middle line:90%
and they spike their blood sugar

00:32:56.608 --> 00:32:58.676 align:middle line:84%
which ultimately
turns into body fat.

00:32:58.676 --> 00:33:00.812 align:middle line:84%
Okay. You couldn't --
it's not healthy for you.

00:33:00.812 --> 00:33:03.048 align:middle line:84%
It's inflammatory
in your organs.

00:33:03.048 --> 00:33:05.417 align:middle line:84%
But wheat bread as well --
it's not the same wheat bread

00:33:05.417 --> 00:33:06.851 align:middle line:90%
that our great-grandmas made.

00:33:06.851 --> 00:33:10.855 align:middle line:84%
It's not that fine corn wheat
that they had in ancient times.

00:33:10.855 --> 00:33:12.791 align:middle line:84%
It's been altered
chemically to make...

00:33:12.791 --> 00:33:14.059 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: More, and more,
and more wheat...

00:33:14.059 --> 00:33:15.794 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: We actually want to
know about breads, right?

00:33:15.794 --> 00:33:18.329 align:middle line:84%
So, they altered it to
make mass production

00:33:18.329 --> 00:33:21.466 align:middle line:84%
and that is linking
people to obesity

00:33:21.466 --> 00:33:24.736 align:middle line:84%
and to inflammation
and arthritis.

00:33:24.736 --> 00:33:26.538 align:middle line:84%
All these hosted
diseases are coming

00:33:26.538 --> 00:33:28.640 align:middle line:84%
from the wheat that
we're consuming.

00:33:28.640 --> 00:33:29.574 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Interesting.

00:33:29.574 --> 00:33:30.909 align:middle line:90%
So, get rid of those things.

00:33:30.909 --> 00:33:33.244 align:middle line:84%
What about condiments and
salad dressings and so forth?

00:33:33.244 --> 00:33:35.814 align:middle line:84%
Do you recommend
making your own?

00:33:35.814 --> 00:33:37.048 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: If you can.

00:33:37.048 --> 00:33:39.584 align:middle line:84%
I know ketchup -- let's
talk about ketchup

00:33:39.584 --> 00:33:41.386 align:middle line:90%
because people love ketchup.

00:33:41.386 --> 00:33:44.189 align:middle line:84%
Those who like ketchup,
like ketchup and they put it

00:33:44.189 --> 00:33:45.857 align:middle line:90%
on everything and that's --

00:33:45.857 --> 00:33:47.859 align:middle line:84%
when I go to people's houses
ketchup's the one thing they're

00:33:47.859 --> 00:33:49.027 align:middle line:90%
like, no.

00:33:49.027 --> 00:33:53.665 align:middle line:84%
You can have your
ketchup, but try to choose,

00:33:53.665 --> 00:33:55.033 align:middle line:90%
you know, that balance.

00:33:55.033 --> 00:33:57.469 align:middle line:84%
Do a little bit of ketchup, but
choose a ketchup that's made

00:33:57.469 --> 00:34:01.706 align:middle line:84%
with no high fructose corn
syrup, and one maybe with Stevia

00:34:01.706 --> 00:34:03.341 align:middle line:90%
or natural sweetener like honey.

00:34:03.341 --> 00:34:05.176 align:middle line:84%
I know people are like,
honey in my ketchup?

00:34:05.176 --> 00:34:07.412 align:middle line:84%
But, you can find those
natural sweeteners in ketchup...

00:34:07.412 --> 00:34:07.945 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Okay.

00:34:07.945 --> 00:34:09.012 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:34:09.012 --> 00:34:10.648 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Yeah, the more
organic ketchups.

00:34:10.648 --> 00:34:11.749 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:34:11.749 --> 00:34:12.983 align:middle line:84%
But not just organic
-- look for the sugars.

00:34:12.983 --> 00:34:15.353 align:middle line:84%
What is in -- what's making
up that organic ketchup?

00:34:15.353 --> 00:34:17.956 align:middle line:84%
Because someone can slap an
organic label on and it's loaded

00:34:17.956 --> 00:34:18.990 align:middle line:90%
with the wrong sugars.

00:34:18.990 --> 00:34:19.523 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Oh.

00:34:19.523 --> 00:34:20.492 align:middle line:90%
Interesting.

00:34:20.492 --> 00:34:22.026 align:middle line:84%
Okay, good to look
at -- look for.

00:34:22.026 --> 00:34:22.659 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:34:22.659 --> 00:34:23.795 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: All right.

00:34:23.795 --> 00:34:25.329 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look at one
of Danette's suggestions

00:34:25.329 --> 00:34:27.030 align:middle line:84%
for healthy chocolate
chip cookies.

00:34:27.030 --> 00:34:28.266 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:34:28.266 --> 00:34:29.367 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: [Background Music] Hi.

00:34:29.367 --> 00:34:32.103 align:middle line:84%
I'm Danette May and
welcome to my kitchen.

00:34:32.103 --> 00:34:33.805 align:middle line:84%
Today I'm going to
share with you one

00:34:33.805 --> 00:34:37.075 align:middle line:84%
of my favorite recipes
that's loaded with protein,

00:34:37.075 --> 00:34:39.344 align:middle line:84%
super healthy for
you and super quick.

00:34:39.344 --> 00:34:41.279 align:middle line:84%
It is chocolate chip
cookie dough.

00:34:41.279 --> 00:34:43.447 align:middle line:90%
Sounds delicious, doesn't it?

00:34:43.447 --> 00:34:44.648 align:middle line:90%
And it is.

00:34:44.648 --> 00:34:47.117 align:middle line:84%
All you have to do is take
about three-fourths cup

00:34:47.117 --> 00:34:49.119 align:middle line:90%
of plain Greek yogurt.

00:34:49.119 --> 00:34:52.123 align:middle line:84%
Greek yogurt is a wonderful
protein source and it's loaded

00:34:52.123 --> 00:34:54.159 align:middle line:84%
with probiotics which
helps with inflammation

00:34:54.159 --> 00:35:02.333 align:middle line:84%
in your gut ultimately leading
you to a flatter stomach.

00:35:02.333 --> 00:35:08.640 align:middle line:84%
Then you're going
to have a tablespoon

00:35:08.640 --> 00:35:14.846 align:middle line:84%
of almond butter another
wonderful protein source

00:35:14.846 --> 00:35:19.817 align:middle line:84%
and a wonderful fat that
you can have in your diet.

00:35:19.817 --> 00:35:22.921 align:middle line:84%
You're going to take
one teaspoon of vanilla

00:35:22.921 --> 00:35:25.390 align:middle line:84%
and a hand full -- you can
see about how much I have,

00:35:25.390 --> 00:35:26.724 align:middle line:84%
handful of dark cocoa
nibs, chocolate chips

00:35:26.724 --> 00:35:27.926 align:middle line:90%
that are 70% higher in cacao.

00:35:27.926 --> 00:35:29.127 align:middle line:84%
Then you're going to take
one teaspoon of Stevia.

00:35:29.127 --> 00:35:30.495 align:middle line:84%
This is a natural
sweetener that I like to use,

00:35:30.495 --> 00:35:31.696 align:middle line:84%
and so you're going to take
all these and mix it together

00:35:31.696 --> 00:35:32.730 align:middle line:84%
in the bowl with the
yogurt, your vanilla,

00:35:32.730 --> 00:35:34.132 align:middle line:90%
and your chocolate chips --

00:35:34.132 --> 00:35:39.003 align:middle line:84%
mix it together and now you have
a delicious tasting chocolate

00:35:39.003 --> 00:35:41.339 align:middle line:90%
chip cookie dough recipe.

00:35:45.577 --> 00:35:46.978 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Okay.

00:35:46.978 --> 00:35:50.114 align:middle line:84%
So, are you a big fan of greens
and a green shake movement --

00:35:50.114 --> 00:35:52.317 align:middle line:84%
all that of the green
juicing movement?

00:35:52.317 --> 00:35:53.384 align:middle line:90%
Did you get into that, as well?

00:35:53.384 --> 00:35:54.919 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Absolutely.

00:35:54.919 --> 00:35:57.622 align:middle line:84%
I think that one of
the missing links

00:35:57.622 --> 00:35:59.958 align:middle line:84%
to our health is not
getting enough greens.

00:35:59.958 --> 00:36:03.995 align:middle line:84%
So, I do love the movement but I
don't encourage anything extreme

00:36:03.995 --> 00:36:06.197 align:middle line:84%
and I think that's what gets
people off track is being

00:36:06.197 --> 00:36:06.898 align:middle line:90%
too extreme.

00:36:06.898 --> 00:36:08.266 align:middle line:90%
So, there's some people

00:36:08.266 --> 00:36:10.635 align:middle line:84%
that that's all they're doing
is green juice all day long

00:36:10.635 --> 00:36:12.804 align:middle line:84%
and that's not sustainable
or healthy as well,

00:36:12.804 --> 00:36:14.305 align:middle line:84%
because you're not
getting enough calories --

00:36:14.305 --> 00:36:15.974 align:middle line:90%
all the different combinations.

00:36:15.974 --> 00:36:19.210 align:middle line:84%
But I do believe in having
greens with every meal...

00:36:19.210 --> 00:36:19.711 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: You do?

00:36:19.711 --> 00:36:20.245 align:middle line:90%
Okay.

00:36:20.245 --> 00:36:21.079 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yes.

00:36:21.079 --> 00:36:22.347 align:middle line:90%
A small portion in every meal.

00:36:22.347 --> 00:36:24.015 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you can take a break
off one because I eat five

00:36:24.015 --> 00:36:25.683 align:middle line:84%
to six times a day
and I encourage people

00:36:25.683 --> 00:36:27.285 align:middle line:90%
to eat five to six times a day.

00:36:27.285 --> 00:36:30.521 align:middle line:84%
Let your body trust you
and fuel it for energy.

00:36:30.521 --> 00:36:33.791 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So does the five to six
times a day set your metabolism

00:36:33.791 --> 00:36:34.592 align:middle line:90%
up in a different way?

00:36:34.592 --> 00:36:36.060 align:middle line:90%
What is the purpose of that?

00:36:36.060 --> 00:36:39.130 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: Well, the purpose is
-- is yeah, like I always say,

00:36:39.130 --> 00:36:41.332 align:middle line:84%
your metabolism is
like this fire.

00:36:41.332 --> 00:36:43.134 align:middle line:84%
Okay, you've got this
slow burning fire.

00:36:43.134 --> 00:36:45.570 align:middle line:84%
If you don't eat, you're
putting the fire out.

00:36:45.570 --> 00:36:46.904 align:middle line:90%
It's starved.

00:36:46.904 --> 00:36:49.507 align:middle line:84%
If you are overeating you're
putting the wrong things --

00:36:49.507 --> 00:36:52.443 align:middle line:84%
it's like this blazing
mass, right?

00:36:52.443 --> 00:36:55.146 align:middle line:84%
So, you want to just keep
this little fire going

00:36:55.146 --> 00:36:56.547 align:middle line:90%
and that's why I do --

00:36:56.547 --> 00:36:59.450 align:middle line:84%
about every two through three
hours I put some protein on it,

00:36:59.450 --> 00:37:02.186 align:middle line:84%
I put some vegetable on it
and it trusts you, right?

00:37:02.186 --> 00:37:04.822 align:middle line:84%
You start to have energy
and then you feed it again,

00:37:04.822 --> 00:37:06.691 align:middle line:84%
and you feed it again,
so you never, like,

00:37:06.691 --> 00:37:08.660 align:middle line:84%
dip low in your blood
sugar levels...

00:37:08.660 --> 00:37:10.495 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: That's a great
way of explaining it --

00:37:10.495 --> 00:37:11.596 align:middle line:90%
you're feeding the fire.

00:37:11.596 --> 00:37:12.697 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Your feeding the fire...

00:37:12.697 --> 00:37:14.465 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And so developing
a trust relationship

00:37:14.465 --> 00:37:15.433 align:middle line:90%
with your metabolism.

00:37:15.433 --> 00:37:16.567 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Absolutely.

00:37:16.567 --> 00:37:18.403 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And, so starving
and going without food

00:37:18.403 --> 00:37:21.906 align:middle line:84%
for long periods of time
is teaching your metabolism

00:37:21.906 --> 00:37:23.341 align:middle line:90%
to not burn.

00:37:23.341 --> 00:37:24.575 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Right.

00:37:24.575 --> 00:37:27.211 align:middle line:84%
Exactly. You're actually
going to hold on to weight.

00:37:27.211 --> 00:37:29.380 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So, how long do
you go between meals?

00:37:29.380 --> 00:37:31.816 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: About every
two to three hours.

00:37:31.816 --> 00:37:33.084 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:37:33.084 --> 00:37:35.119 align:middle line:84%
That's amazing -- and you
learn to just keep that up

00:37:35.119 --> 00:37:36.020 align:middle line:90%
and keep that going...

