00:39:38.576 --> 00:39:39.710 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: I do it morning
and night.

00:39:39.710 --> 00:39:42.613 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And that fuels
the metabolism again,

00:39:42.613 --> 00:39:43.648 align:middle line:90%
right, I could see that.

00:39:43.648 --> 00:39:45.049 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Absolutely.

00:39:45.049 --> 00:39:47.018 align:middle line:84%
The cayenne, like, brings up the
oxygen consumption in your body.

00:39:47.018 --> 00:39:49.887 align:middle line:84%
Within 20 minutes of
consuming cayenne your

00:39:49.887 --> 00:39:51.055 align:middle line:90%
metabolism increases.

00:39:51.055 --> 00:39:53.257 align:middle line:84%
It's a little fire,
a little engager.

00:39:53.257 --> 00:39:56.194 align:middle line:84%
And the turmeric is helping
with inflammation, so, you know,

00:39:56.194 --> 00:40:00.098 align:middle line:84%
a lot of people are walking
around with distended abdomens,

00:40:00.098 --> 00:40:01.532 align:middle line:84%
not because they're
really overweight --

00:40:01.532 --> 00:40:02.800 align:middle line:90%
because they're inflamed.

00:40:02.800 --> 00:40:05.703 align:middle line:84%
They're building up toxins
for all the wrong things,

00:40:05.703 --> 00:40:07.538 align:middle line:84%
so turmeric is going
to help with that

00:40:07.538 --> 00:40:10.741 align:middle line:84%
and the lemon's going
to help with that.

