at the same time?

00:40:32.497 --> 00:40:35.132 align:middle line:84%
Today I want to show you
exercise movements you can do

00:40:35.132 --> 00:40:37.268 align:middle line:84%
to tone up the whole
section of your arm

00:40:37.268 --> 00:40:39.003 align:middle line:90%
without doing a single push up.

00:40:39.003 --> 00:40:41.172 align:middle line:84%
You cannot believe how
great this movement is.

00:40:41.172 --> 00:40:43.975 align:middle line:84%
I learned it from the beautiful
[inaudible] and you will see

00:40:43.975 --> 00:40:47.378 align:middle line:84%
for yourself, doing this with
me how this is really going

00:40:47.378 --> 00:40:48.579 align:middle line:90%
to tone up your arm.

00:40:48.579 --> 00:40:50.681 align:middle line:84%
First off, you're going to
just take your arms out.

00:40:50.681 --> 00:40:52.583 align:middle line:84%
You're going to do
circles forward.

00:40:52.583 --> 00:40:55.019 align:middle line:84%
You're going to circle
forward for 30 seconds.

00:40:55.019 --> 00:40:57.855 align:middle line:84%
I know this seems like, how
can this really affect me?

00:40:57.855 --> 00:40:59.657 align:middle line:84%
If you do this you
will find out.

00:40:59.657 --> 00:41:02.693 align:middle line:84%
After that 30 seconds,
you're going to go backwards.

00:41:02.693 --> 00:41:05.763 align:middle line:84%
Okay. Opposite direction
for 30 seconds.

00:41:05.763 --> 00:41:09.133 align:middle line:84%
Your arms are going to feel
hot at this point, okay?

00:41:09.133 --> 00:41:11.302 align:middle line:84%
Once you've hit 30
seconds going back,

00:41:11.302 --> 00:41:13.538 align:middle line:84%
bring your hands
up to a goal post.

00:41:13.538 --> 00:41:15.840 align:middle line:84%
You're going to reach
up and then pretend

00:41:15.840 --> 00:41:17.241 align:middle line:84%
like you're pulling
something down.

00:41:17.241 --> 00:41:21.112 align:middle line:84%
You can see that my biceps have
started to engage, then reach

00:41:21.112 --> 00:41:22.647 align:middle line:90%
and just go that goal post.

00:41:22.647 --> 00:41:24.849 align:middle line:90%
Down. Up. And down.

00:41:24.849 --> 00:41:25.917 align:middle line:90%
Beautiful.

00:41:25.917 --> 00:41:28.486 align:middle line:84%
Up and down -- doing
this for 30 seconds.

00:41:28.486 --> 00:41:30.688 align:middle line:84%
After you've done this,
now they're really

00:41:30.688 --> 00:41:32.623 align:middle line:90%
on fire, but hang with me.

00:41:32.623 --> 00:41:38.162 align:middle line:84%
Stay here with your goal posts,
then come forward out, and in.

00:41:38.162 --> 00:41:39.030 align:middle line:90%
Very good.

00:41:39.030 --> 00:41:40.131 align:middle line:90%
This is starting work.

00:41:40.131 --> 00:41:42.133 align:middle line:90%
Now your pectorals muscle.

00:41:42.133 --> 00:41:44.502 align:middle line:84%
You're going to do
this for 30 seconds.

00:41:44.502 --> 00:41:47.805 align:middle line:84%
Yes. As you're doing this
forward and back motion,

00:41:47.805 --> 00:41:50.942 align:middle line:84%
you're also getting the
back part of your back.

00:41:50.942 --> 00:41:53.144 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to turn
around so you can see.

00:41:53.144 --> 00:41:55.680 align:middle line:84%
I'm squeezing and
going forward and back.

00:41:55.680 --> 00:41:57.248 align:middle line:90%
I'm not just doing the motion,

00:41:57.248 --> 00:42:02.453 align:middle line:84%
but I'm really pushing
back and front.

00:42:02.453 --> 00:42:04.288 align:middle line:90%
So, I am actually flexing.

00:42:04.288 --> 00:42:08.526 align:middle line:84%
You can see my bicep right her
is engaged going front and back.

00:42:08.526 --> 00:42:13.230 align:middle line:84%
At this point after 30 seconds
bring everything together.

00:42:13.230 --> 00:42:14.966 align:middle line:90%
My elbows stay together.

00:42:14.966 --> 00:42:16.167 align:middle line:90%
That is key.

00:42:16.167 --> 00:42:17.702 align:middle line:90%
Hands are right here.

00:42:17.702 --> 00:42:20.071 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to lift and lower.

00:42:20.071 --> 00:42:22.139 align:middle line:90%
Try to get your elbows up to

00:42:22.139 --> 00:42:25.109 align:middle line:84%
at least your jaw line
keeping your elbows together.

00:42:25.109 --> 00:42:29.914 align:middle line:84%
I haven't even done the full 30
seconds and I'm feeling this.

00:42:29.914 --> 00:42:34.385 align:middle line:84%
You can do this workout
anywhere at any time

00:42:34.385 --> 00:42:37.622 align:middle line:84%
and truly see benefits
in your arms.

