00:52:57.841 --> 00:53:00.177 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: They're great for
kid's lunch boxes as well.

00:53:00.177 --> 00:53:01.612 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Absolutely.

00:53:01.612 --> 00:53:06.049 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: You can add things
like almonds or walnuts,

00:53:06.049 --> 00:53:07.251 align:middle line:90%
probably walnuts are better.

00:53:07.251 --> 00:53:09.853 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: I do unsweetened,
shredded coconut in there

00:53:09.853 --> 00:53:11.255 align:middle line:90%
if you want a little Hawaiian.

00:53:11.255 --> 00:53:14.224 align:middle line:84%
Some macadamia nuts -- you can
do a lot of different things.

00:53:14.224 --> 00:53:15.559 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Nice.

00:53:15.559 --> 00:53:17.494 align:middle line:84%
Nice. Do you have -- when
you're cooking for the holidays,

00:53:17.494 --> 00:53:20.664 align:middle line:84%
do you ever have big
meals during the holidays?

00:53:20.664 --> 00:53:22.833 align:middle line:84%
Do you ever have time where
it's just not possible

00:53:22.833 --> 00:53:24.434 align:middle line:90%
to have the six meals a day?

00:53:24.434 --> 00:53:25.669 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Absolutely.

00:53:25.669 --> 00:53:28.739 align:middle line:84%
You got to be, like I
said, loving to yourself --

00:53:28.739 --> 00:53:32.376 align:middle line:84%
my best friend would say,
Danette is so strict I'm sure,

00:53:32.376 --> 00:53:35.245 align:middle line:84%
Danette -- and she
was like, "No.

00:53:35.245 --> 00:53:37.281 align:middle line:84%
Actually she -- I
love carrot cake.

00:53:37.281 --> 00:53:38.348 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about this.

00:53:38.348 --> 00:53:39.383 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Okay, okay.

00:53:39.383 --> 00:53:40.384 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: If someone
is going to offer me

00:53:40.384 --> 00:53:41.685 align:middle line:90%
that I have a carrot cake.

00:53:41.685 --> 00:53:43.754 align:middle line:84%
I enjoy it and I don't
feel guilty about it.

00:53:43.754 --> 00:53:44.388 align:middle line:90%
I don't...

00:53:44.388 --> 00:53:45.155 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: You don't?

00:53:45.155 --> 00:53:46.223 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: ...stress about it

00:53:46.223 --> 00:53:47.157 align:middle line:84%
but I'm not eating
carrot cake every day

00:53:47.157 --> 00:53:48.558 align:middle line:84%
and I'm not eating
it every week.

00:53:48.558 --> 00:53:51.862 align:middle line:84%
But I do enjoy -- and there are
times you can't control things.

00:53:51.862 --> 00:53:53.497 align:middle line:90%
But that's okay.

00:53:53.497 --> 00:53:55.065 align:middle line:90%
Just conquer your own kitchen.

00:53:55.065 --> 00:53:56.466 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So, you don't
make up for the day --

00:53:56.466 --> 00:53:58.468 align:middle line:90%
say you had carrot cake at night

00:53:58.468 --> 00:54:00.704 align:middle line:84%
and the next day you
don't skip a meal.

00:54:00.704 --> 00:54:01.772 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Absolutely not.

00:54:01.772 --> 00:54:03.073 align:middle line:90%
But I will move.

00:54:03.073 --> 00:54:06.510 align:middle line:84%
I do know intuitively --
okay, I just ate carrot cake

00:54:06.510 --> 00:54:08.245 align:middle line:84%
and that had a lot
of sugar in it.

00:54:08.245 --> 00:54:09.746 align:middle line:84%
My body doesn't really
want sugar.

00:54:09.746 --> 00:54:11.481 align:middle line:90%
None of our bodies want sugar.

00:54:11.481 --> 00:54:15.085 align:middle line:84%
So, I will try to go for a
walk after that meal, you know.

00:54:15.085 --> 00:54:16.687 align:middle line:84%
If I'm with family I'll
be like, "Hey guys.

00:54:16.687 --> 00:54:18.622 align:middle line:84%
You want to go for a
little night walk?"

00:54:18.622 --> 00:54:19.990 align:middle line:90%
"Go look at the moon?"

00:54:19.990 --> 00:54:22.592 align:middle line:84%
I try to bring in movement in
there because I want to get

00:54:22.592 --> 00:54:25.829 align:middle line:84%
that body going to burn
up the sugars instead

00:54:25.829 --> 00:54:27.230 align:middle line:84%
of letting them convert
right into fat

00:54:27.230 --> 00:54:28.498 align:middle line:90%
and sit in my bloodstream.

00:54:28.498 --> 00:54:30.133 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Now, you live in
an area that has a lot

00:54:30.133 --> 00:54:32.035 align:middle line:90%
of snow -- you're in Utah.

00:54:32.035 --> 00:54:34.838 align:middle line:84%
So what do you do when
there's nowhere to go outside

00:54:34.838 --> 00:54:35.939 align:middle line:90%
or if it's snowing or something?

00:54:35.939 --> 00:54:37.808 align:middle line:90%
Do you do indoor exercises also?

00:54:37.808 --> 00:54:39.142 align:middle line:90%
Other than skiing...

00:54:39.142 --> 00:54:41.678 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: Yeah, you know, and
what I have this philosophy --

00:54:41.678 --> 00:54:44.815 align:middle line:84%
and I make my kids do it --
every day you go outside.

00:54:44.815 --> 00:54:47.484 align:middle line:84%
I don't care if it's raining,
snowing, we're not going

00:54:47.484 --> 00:54:51.188 align:middle line:84%
to melt -- get your coat on,
because nature is a healer.

00:54:51.188 --> 00:54:54.124 align:middle line:84%
And you're really going to
receive a lot of inspiration

00:54:54.124 --> 00:54:57.361 align:middle line:84%
and stay on point with healthy
eating and exercising just

00:54:57.361 --> 00:54:58.795 align:middle line:90%
by getting out in nature.

00:54:58.795 --> 00:54:59.863 align:middle line:90%
You're going to feel better,

00:54:59.863 --> 00:55:02.065 align:middle line:84%
so put on your clothes
and go for a walk.

00:55:02.065 --> 00:55:04.801 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: It's been interesting,
because within the first 10

00:55:04.801 --> 00:55:07.904 align:middle line:84%
to 15 minutes of exercise
the endorphins release.

00:55:07.904 --> 00:55:09.773 align:middle line:84%
The happy chemicals
start to flow

00:55:09.773 --> 00:55:11.475 align:middle line:90%
in your brain and in your body.

00:55:11.475 --> 00:55:14.444 align:middle line:84%
It will completely shift
my mood within 15 minutes.

00:55:14.444 --> 00:55:15.645 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:55:15.645 --> 00:55:17.047 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: I can actually
feel the shift happening.

00:55:17.047 --> 00:55:20.083 align:middle line:84%
I can feel negativity,
or whatever it is

00:55:20.083 --> 00:55:23.020 align:middle line:84%
that I've got going with my
day -- up until that workout,

00:55:23.020 --> 00:55:26.556 align:middle line:84%
15 minutes in I'm in a
completely different mood.

00:55:26.556 --> 00:55:27.758 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: It's powerful.

00:55:27.758 --> 00:55:29.059 align:middle line:90%
It is power.

00:55:29.059 --> 00:55:31.361 align:middle line:84%
And the thing to remember is
we don't have to exercise.

00:55:31.361 --> 00:55:33.063 align:middle line:90%
We don't have to eat well.

00:55:33.063 --> 00:55:34.364 align:middle line:90%
We get to.

00:55:34.364 --> 00:55:36.933 align:middle line:84%
It's our choice and once you
say, "This is my choice."

00:55:36.933 --> 00:55:39.436 align:middle line:84%
All that other drama
goes out the door.

00:55:39.436 --> 00:55:42.305 align:middle line:84%
Trying to overthink it or
when am I going to get it

00:55:42.305 --> 00:55:43.774 align:middle line:90%
in -- I get to do this.

00:55:43.774 --> 00:55:49.613 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: That's a great point --
but I loved it when you said,

00:55:49.613 --> 00:55:51.882 align:middle line:84%
"Abs, good abs are
made in the kitchen."

00:55:51.882 --> 00:55:53.683 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: It's true.

00:55:53.683 --> 00:55:55.585 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: That's perfect
because it's true.

00:55:55.585 --> 00:55:57.387 align:middle line:84%
All the inflammation
around our guts

00:55:57.387 --> 00:55:59.389 align:middle line:84%
and so forth you can get
rid of with the foods

00:55:59.389 --> 00:56:01.491 align:middle line:84%
that you're eating -- the
cleansing food and the drink

00:56:01.491 --> 00:56:02.893 align:middle line:90%
that you made as well.

00:56:02.893 --> 00:56:04.161 align:middle line:84%
And you do that twice
a day, right?

00:56:04.161 --> 00:56:05.228 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: Yeah.

00:56:05.228 --> 00:56:06.830 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Now, do you
ever do protein shakes,

00:56:06.830 --> 00:56:08.365 align:middle line:84%
different types of
protein powders?

00:56:08.365 --> 00:56:11.268 align:middle line:84%
Do you recommend
anything, whey, not whey?

00:56:11.268 --> 00:56:14.037 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: I definitely don't do
soy and I have a whole section

00:56:14.037 --> 00:56:17.274 align:middle line:84%
in my book about why
I don't choose soy.

00:56:17.274 --> 00:56:19.776 align:middle line:84%
So I choose a whey
protein and I do protein.

00:56:19.776 --> 00:56:22.512 align:middle line:84%
I don't always to
a protein shake,

00:56:22.512 --> 00:56:25.315 align:middle line:84%
but it is a really great
option if you're on the go.

00:56:25.315 --> 00:56:26.716 align:middle line:90%
It's so much better

00:56:26.716 --> 00:56:30.520 align:middle line:84%
than choosing the alternatives
sometimes because -- there is --

00:56:30.520 --> 00:56:33.590 align:middle line:84%
you know once again, I want a
protein if I don't have time

00:56:33.590 --> 00:56:35.792 align:middle line:84%
to have something that takes
a little longer then a protein

00:56:35.792 --> 00:56:36.660 align:middle line:90%
shake is a great source.

00:56:36.660 --> 00:56:38.128 align:middle line:90%
You can throw fruit in there.

00:56:38.128 --> 00:56:41.331 align:middle line:84%
I love throwing chia in
there which is wonderful --

00:56:41.331 --> 00:56:43.233 align:middle line:84%
and so, vegetables
too you can throw them

00:56:43.233 --> 00:56:44.134 align:middle line:90%
and mask them in there.

00:56:44.134 --> 00:56:45.435 align:middle line:90%
I do spinach in every smoothie.

00:56:45.435 --> 00:56:46.136 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Oh.

00:56:46.136 --> 00:56:46.970 align:middle line:90%
That's a great idea .

00:56:46.970 --> 00:56:47.637 align:middle line:90%
>> DM: And you never taste it.

00:56:47.637 --> 00:56:49.005 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: That's right.

00:56:49.005 --> 00:56:52.609 align:middle line:84%
Well, thank you so much for
your tools, your information,

00:56:52.609 --> 00:56:54.110 align:middle line:90%
your inspiration, everything.

00:56:54.110 --> 00:56:55.078 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

00:56:55.078 --> 00:56:56.613 align:middle line:84%
>> DM: Thank you
for having me, Lisa.

00:56:56.613 --> 00:56:57.747 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Absolutely.

